ul.li:
A set of quota keys for specifying quota limit. For example, ec2:vmnumber evaluates to the current instance numbers for the request identity (user, group or account). You can only use NumericLessThanEquals condition type for quota keys, as noted in the following example condition block:
"Condition": {
    "NumericLessThanEquals": {
        ec2:vmnumber”: "12"
     }
}

This example states that that the principal cannot launch more than 12 instances. Depending on what identity the policy is attached to, the key evaluates at different levels. For example, if the above policy condition is attached to a group, then the ec2:vmnumber is evaluated for the group.
